message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Tunisia in the past 5 years was the Tunisian Revolution, also known as the Jasmine Revolution, which began in late 2010 and led to the overthrow of President Zine El Abidine Ben Ali in January 2011. This event sparked a wave of pro-democracy movements across the Arab world, known as the Arab Spring. The Tunisian Revolution marked a turning point in the country's history, leading to the establishment of a democratic system and the adoption of a new constitution.
